        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 3A–M. Egaenus oedipus (Thorell, 1876), male. A–D Habitus (A dorsal, B ventral, C frontal, D lateral). E Eye mound, dorsal. F, G Right chelicera (F mesal, G lateral). H, I Right pedipalp (H mesal, I lateral). J–K Penis (J dorsal, K lateral). L, M Close-up of penis glans (L dorsal, M lateral). Scale lines: A–D: 1 mm; E–I: 0.5 mm; J–K: 0.5 mm; L, M: 0.1 mm." ;
